    <descriptionSet>
      <description>This printed book of hours offered the owner not just a cycle of prayers but medical advice as well, including when to be bled. Zodiacal Man’s midsection indicates which planets rule which parts of the body: Jupiter affects his liver, the moon his head, and so on. The smaller figures at the corners are types of the four humors. Doctors as far back as Hippocrates knew that an imbalance of the body’s four fluids, known as humors, resulted in distortions of health and character.</description>
